<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="122" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1704,2019]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">
The name 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1782" box="[320,690,1740,1766]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripustulata">
<emphasis box="[320,578,1740,1766]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Scolia quadripustulata</emphasis>
Fabricius
</taxonomicName>
was misapplied for a long time to another species now known as 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius. The" authorityYear="1804" box="[151,384,1776,1803]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="binotata">
<emphasis box="[151,272,1776,1803]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">S. binotata</emphasis>
Fabricius
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gupta, S. K. &amp; Jonathan, J. K." box="[398,679,1776,1803]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" refId="ref14969" refString="Gupta, S. K. &amp; Jonathan, J. K. (2003) Fauna of India and the adjacent countries, Hymenoptera: Scoliidae. The Director, Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata, 277 pp." type="book" year="2003">Gupta &amp; Jonathan, 2003</bibRefCitation>
). We checked all specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1059,1126,1776,1802]" name="China" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">China</collectingCountry>
in IOZ and RMNH, and all were found to belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius. The" authorityName="Fabricius. The" authorityYear="1804" box="[421,877,1812,1838]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="binotata" subGenus="Discolia">
<emphasis box="[421,710,1812,1838]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Scolia (Discolia) binotata</emphasis>
Fabricius. The
</taxonomicName>
following characters may be used to separate both species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1704,2019]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">
The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius. The" authorityYear="1804" box="[344,466,1884,1911]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="binotata">
<emphasis box="[344,466,1884,1911]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">S. binotata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[483,744,1884,1911]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 5" captionStart-1="FIGURE 1" captionStart-2="FIGURE 2" captionStart-3="FIGURE 3" captionStart-4="FIGURE 4" captionStartId-0="20.[151,250,1202,1226]" captionStartId-1="5.[151,250,1967,1991]" captionStartId-2="6.[151,250,1633,1657]" captionStartId-3="18.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionStartId-4="19.[151,250,1474,1498]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,310,1179]" captionTargetBox-1="[171,1416,179,1932]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,181,1610]" captionTargetBox-3="[151,1436,416,1891]" captionTargetBox-4="[151,1436,181,1450]" captionTargetId-0="figure-63@20.[151,1436,309,1179]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@5.[171,1416,179,1941]" captionTargetId-2="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1610]" captionTargetId-3="figure-95@18.[151,1436,416,1901]" captionTargetId-4="figure-19@19.[151,1436,181,1450]" captionTargetPageId-0="20" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionTargetPageId-2="6" captionTargetPageId-3="18" captionTargetPageId-4="19" captionText-0="FIGURE 5. a1–a3 and b1–b3: male of Scolia (Discolia) binotata Fabricius, 1804 (misidentified by Betrem), a1, b1. habitus, dorsal aspect; a2, b2. male genitalia, ventral aspect; a3, b3. male genitalia, dorsal aspect. c1–c4 (misidentified by Betrem) and d1–d3: female of S. (D.) binotata Fabricius, 1804, c1, d1. habitus, dorsal aspect; c2, d2. head, antero-dorsal aspect; c3, d3. mesosoma, dorsal aspect; c4. metapleuron, lateral aspect." captionText-1="FIGURE 1. Male of Colpa cf. mongolica (Morawitz, 1889) from China, a. habitus, dorsal aspect; b. mesosoma, lateral aspect; c. mesosoma, dorsal aspect; d. fore wing." captionText-2="FIGURE 2. Female of Colpa tartara (de Saussure, 1880) from East Kazakhstan, a. head, anterior aspect; b. head, dorsal aspect; c. habitus, dorsal aspect;. head and mesosoma, lateral aspect; e. fore wing." captionText-3="FIGURE 3. Male of C. (C.) collaris quadrifasciata (Fabricius, 1798) from West Malaysia, a. habitus, dorsal aspect; b. habitus, lateral aspect; c. mesosoma, dorsal aspect; d. head, dorsal aspect; e. mesopleuron and metapleuron, lateral aspect; f. label; g. 8th sternite and male genitalia, ventral aspect; h. 8th sternite and male genitalia, dorsal aspect." captionText-4="FIGURE 4. Female of C. (C.) collaris quadrifasciata (Fabricius, 1798) from Thailand, a. habitus, dorsal aspect; b. mesosoma, dorsal aspect; c. head, dorsal aspect; d. head, anterior aspect." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736266" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736254" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736256" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736260" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736262" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4736266/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4736254/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/4736256/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/4736260/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/4736262/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 5a1–5a3, 5b1–5b3</figureCitation>
) has the erect vestiture predominantly white on the head and mesosoma (vestiture on head and mesosoma black in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1782" box="[780,990,1920,1947]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripustulata">
<emphasis box="[780,990,1920,1947]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">S. quadripustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and antennal flagellum short, clavate towards apex, and penultimate segments as broad as long (flagellum distinctly longer and not clavate towards apex and penultimate segments longer than broad in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1782" box="[682,889,1992,2019]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripustulata">
<emphasis box="[682,889,1992,2019]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">S. quadripustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,150,357]" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">
The female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius. The" authorityYear="1804" box="[359,478,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="binotata">
<emphasis box="[359,478,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">S. binotata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[493,735,150,177]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 5" captionStart-1="FIGURE 1" captionStart-2="FIGURE 2" captionStart-3="FIGURE 3" captionStart-4="FIGURE 4" captionStartId-0="20.[151,250,1202,1226]" captionStartId-1="5.[151,250,1967,1991]" captionStartId-2="6.[151,250,1633,1657]" captionStartId-3="18.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionStartId-4="19.[151,250,1474,1498]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,310,1179]" captionTargetBox-1="[171,1416,179,1932]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,181,1610]" captionTargetBox-3="[151,1436,416,1891]" captionTargetBox-4="[151,1436,181,1450]" captionTargetId-0="figure-63@20.[151,1436,309,1179]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@5.[171,1416,179,1941]" captionTargetId-2="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1610]" captionTargetId-3="figure-95@18.[151,1436,416,1901]" captionTargetId-4="figure-19@19.[151,1436,181,1450]" captionTargetPageId-0="20" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionTargetPageId-2="6" captionTargetPageId-3="18" captionTargetPageId-4="19" captionText-0="FIGURE 5. a1–a3 and b1–b3: male of Scolia (Discolia) binotata Fabricius, 1804 (misidentified by Betrem), a1, b1. habitus, dorsal aspect; a2, b2. male genitalia, ventral aspect; a3, b3. male genitalia, dorsal aspect. c1–c4 (misidentified by Betrem) and d1–d3: female of S. (D.) binotata Fabricius, 1804, c1, d1. habitus, dorsal aspect; c2, d2. head, antero-dorsal aspect; c3, d3. mesosoma, dorsal aspect; c4. metapleuron, lateral aspect." captionText-1="FIGURE 1. Male of Colpa cf. mongolica (Morawitz, 1889) from China, a. habitus, dorsal aspect; b. mesosoma, lateral aspect; c. mesosoma, dorsal aspect; d. fore wing." captionText-2="FIGURE 2. Female of Colpa tartara (de Saussure, 1880) from East Kazakhstan, a. head, anterior aspect; b. head, dorsal aspect; c. habitus, dorsal aspect;. head and mesosoma, lateral aspect; e. fore wing." captionText-3="FIGURE 3. Male of C. (C.) collaris quadrifasciata (Fabricius, 1798) from West Malaysia, a. habitus, dorsal aspect; b. habitus, lateral aspect; c. mesosoma, dorsal aspect; d. head, dorsal aspect; e. mesopleuron and metapleuron, lateral aspect; f. label; g. 8th sternite and male genitalia, ventral aspect; h. 8th sternite and male genitalia, dorsal aspect." captionText-4="FIGURE 4. Female of C. (C.) collaris quadrifasciata (Fabricius, 1798) from Thailand, a. habitus, dorsal aspect; b. mesosoma, dorsal aspect; c. head, dorsal aspect; d. head, anterior aspect." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736266" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736254" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736256" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736260" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736262" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4736266/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4736254/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/4736256/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/4736260/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/4736262/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">Fig. 5c1–5c, 5d1–5d3</figureCitation>
) has the pronotum dorso-posteriorly (“scapulae”) and posterior half of mesoscutum medially and scutellum with a few scattered punctures(densely punctate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1782" box="[1179,1383,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripustulata">
<emphasis box="[1179,1383,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">S.quadripustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with small impunctate area on scutellum medio-posteriorly), anterior rim of clypeus broadly rounded anteriorly (anterior rim of clypeus truncate anteriorly in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1782" box="[582,793,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripustulata">
<emphasis box="[582,793,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">S. quadripustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and metapleuron largely impunctate (subcontiguously punctate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1782" box="[278,483,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripustulata">
<emphasis box="[278,483,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">S. quadripustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). All reported records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1782" box="[759,964,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripustulata">
<emphasis box="[759,964,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">S. quadripustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1029,1096,295,321]" name="China" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">China</collectingCountry>
concern 
<emphasis box="[1194,1323,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius. The" authorityYear="1804" box="[1194,1315,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="binotata">S. binotata</taxonomicName>
;
</emphasis>
therefore, we delete 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1782" box="[265,472,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Scoliidae" genus="Scolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripustulata">
<emphasis box="[265,472,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="122">S. quadripustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Chinese checklist.
</paragraph>
